      "level": {
        "value": 11
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (C10):</strong> a bogeyman 'tourist' from Lepidstadt who chased Scarwall's legend, got snared by the curse — and has convinced himself that staying is <em>his</em> idea. The torture room's racks and iron maidens stay in perfect working order for him; spirit-skulled orcs he catches learn why. <strong>Tactics:</strong> he occupies the party with whispers and holds while focusing his gaze on the <strong>highest-Charisma PC</strong> (the one most worth tormenting to madness). <strong>At 30 HP or fewer he flees</strong> deep into the castle by Mist Escape, recovers, stalks the party with <em>nightmare</em> dreams — and returns for a rematch, preferably after recruiting another Scarwall denizen to help.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
